adjectives.description: unarresting (comparative more unarresting, superlative most unarresting)

entries.meaning: Not arresting; that does not hold the attention.
examples: […]  a meagre and monotonous evangelism — shunning to declare the whole counsel of God, or reiterating a few favourite phrases till they grow as trite and unarresting as a cuckoo-song — has provoked that fatal falsehood  […]
